main event: Two luminous circular-oval objects were spotted traveling from West to East at altitudes estimated to be 20,000 feet over Presque Isle, Maine, in October 1952.
interesting points: The objects emitted intermittent red and green lights,The sighting lasted for approximately 2.5 hours,The speed of the objects appeared to be greater than 600 mph,Observers noted the strange shape of the objects during the sighting,There was insufficient data to determine the exact nature or origin of the objects.
witness description: Observers stated they sighted the objects.
